<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3641] Ruby client should try to connect to every result of getaddrinfo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3641</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ruby Socket::open only tries to connect to the first result of ::Socket::getaddrinfo and throw TTransportException without trying the rest of all.&lt;br/&gt;
It should instead iterate the result until it finds connectable one or reach to the end.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
